<Content>Pure luxury Loved the luxury in the hotel -receptionists need some attention though! We stayed here for a 4 day tour of Barcelona. Booked the hotel based on reviews on Tripadvisor and they were generally bang on .Magnificent bedroom, really spotless and beautifully furnished.Breakfast was steep at 17e extra each so we ate in a really nice tapas bar 20 metres down the street. Room service excellent.It is in a very nice district ,if a little far away, maybe 15 mins walk to the La Rambla hive of activity. We had pretty wet cold weather so we soon got used to using the metro to travel from the hotel to the main attractions just 2 stops away.If I were going again I think I would rather compromise on the luxury to get a more central location.There's so much to see!The only gripe I have about this hotel is the reception. The evening we arrived the receptionist could not locate our booking .When I showed her our copy which I had printed out from the website she sighed and agreed that it would be okay because there was plenty of availability anyway.There was definitely no sign of a remotely friendly welcome. Again on our departure we were coldly sent on our way . When we returned later to get our bags we again encountered the same dismissive attitude.Nevertheless if you want real luxury, huge firm beds, comfy surroundings and fabulous food go for it - just ignore the lack of friendliness !! 
