<Author>Desertgirl1960
<Content>Great Hotel! My husband and I stayed at the Barcelona Center Hotel for 4 nights during our 25th anniversary trip to Spain and Italy in Sept. 2007. We arrived at the hotel at about 11 a.m. and our room was ready which was a great relief since we flew all night and were exhausted. The hotel is located in the Eixample district - an easy 10 min. walk to the Placa de Catalunya, La Ramblas and the waterfront but away from all the noise and craziness of Las Ramblas. There were plenty of restaurants/bars/cafes nearby as well as shopping. The hotel is located on the corner of Calle Mallorca. We were never disturbed by outside noise or other guests. It was remarkably quiet which was great after long, exhausting days sightseeing.The room was perfect - it faced a very pretty courtyard and had clearly been recently remodeled. It was very clean and modern with a large flatscreen TV, a safe and 2 built-in wardrobes. The bathroom was spotless and the shower pressure and hot water was plentiful any time of day.The breakfast was included in our price. There was a good selection of foods, both hot and cold. The only thing we didn't care for was the very runny scrambled eggs (this seems to be the standard in Europe). We did not eat at the hotel restaurant.The hotel provided internet service. A little pricey but very convenient and it was always available when we wanted to use it. I didn't see any internet cafes on the street like there are in Rome but maybe we just weren't looking in the right places.We bought tickets for the hop-on hop-off open-air bus on the first day and it was a great way to familiarize ourselves with the city and get from place to place. We did not use the metro system.We did book a day trip to Torres Winery, Monserrat (a monastery in the mountains) and Sitges (a small town by the sea just south of Barcelona). The winery was about an hour outside of Barcelona and very nice. Monserrat sits high on a mountain and the views are breathtaking. The boys choir sings every day at 1 p.m. and was amazing to listen to. Sitges has alot of history and architecture and the beaches there were beautiful. I would highly recommend this day trip.All in all, the Barcelona Center Hotel was a great place to stay and if we ever return to Barcelona, we will definitely stay there again. 
